  "task": "Write a self-contained Deno TypeScript program that imports from src/life-types.ts and src/life-runner.ts. Define 8+ entity genomes and a decision function. Run a 200-tick simulation on a 40x30 world with 80 initial resources. The decision function must: (1) keep entities alive by harvesting resources, (2) create visually interesting trail patterns that score well on beauty metrics (symmetry, complexity, rhythm, color harmony, coverage), (3) balance survival and aesthetics. Output JSON on last line: {\"fitness\": 0-1, \"branches\": 1, \"survivalRate\": 0-1, \"beautyScore\": 0-1, \"efficiency\": 0-1}",
  "scoringLogic": "survivalRate(0.5) + beautyTotal(0.3) + harvestEfficiency(0.2)",
  "difficulty": 3,
  "passThreshold": 0.3
}
